Russia’s RTS Stock-Index Futures Gain as Oil Rises in New York

-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 
2011-02-15T16:36:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/russia-s-rts-stock-index-futures-gain-as-oil-rises-in-new-york.html
  Russia ’s RTS stock-index futures
rose after two days of declines as oil, the country’s main
export earner, gained in New York and London.  Futures on the RTS Index expiring in March increased 0.2
percent to 185,015 at 11:15 a.m. in New York. The Market Vectors
Russia ETF, a U.S.-traded fund that holds Russian shares, sank
0.7 percent. Futures on OAO Lukoil, the country’s second-biggest
oil producer, rose 0.1 percent and contracts on OAO Gazprom,
Russia’s natural-gas export monopoly, gained 0.1 percent.  Crude advanced 0.6 percent, to $85.28 a barrel on the  New
York Mercantile Exchange . Brent crude for April settlement
gained 0.5 percent, to $103.58 a barrel on the London-based ICE
Futures Europe exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
